Well, that's jest as easy to larn now, sence you
see I'm mending my bridle, and looking arter my
critter
that's been stolen, I reckon, by some thieving
soldiers
saving
your presence, and axing your pardon.
What soldiers?
Why, how do I know? Sometimes they're one
thing, sometimes another; now they're whigs, and
now they're tories. One time they're Gainey's,
another
